segment.name: Beginning of message
segment.documentation: BGM, A segment by which the sender uniquely identifies the Quality Data Message by means of its type and number.

segment.name: Date/time/period
segment.documentation:
DTM, A segment specifying general dates and, when relevant, times related to the whole message. The segment must be specified at least once to identify the quality data message date.
Example of the use of this DTM-segment is : date/time frame of reported data that apply to the whole quality data message.
The Date/time/period segment within other segment groups should be used whenever the date/time/period requires to be logically related to another specified data item; e.g. date of measurement must be specified within the measurement segment group.

segment.name: Item description
segment.documentation: IMD, A segment for describing the product involved.

segment.name: Measurements
segment.documentation: MEA, A segment to allow physical measurements and dimensions to be stated, where this is required for identification of the product.

segment.name: Free text
segment.documentation: FTX, A segment with free text information, in coded or clear form, to give further clarification, when required, to the whole message. In computer to computer exchanges such text will normally require the receiver to handle this segment manually.

segmentGroup.documentation: Segment Group 1: A segment group for referencing documents and where necessary, their dates, relating to the whole message, e.g. purchase order, shipment/consignment number.

segment.name: Reference
segment.documentation: RFF, A segment identifying the referenced document by its number and where appropriate, a line number within that document.

segment.name: Date/time/period
segment.documentation: DTM, A segment specifying the date/time of the referenced document. The specified date should be in 'yymmdd' format, unless all parties agree that there is a functional requirement for an alternative format.

segmentGroup.documentation: Segment Group 2: A group of segments identifying the parties relevant to the whole Quality Data Message, with associated information.

segment.name: Name and address
segment.documentation: NAD, A segment identifying names and addresses of parties, in coded or clear form, and their function relevant for the whole Quality Data Message. Identification of the Sender and Receiver party is mandatory for the Quality Data Message. They are to be given in the NAD segment.

segment.name: Place/location identification
segment.documentation: LOC, A segment indicating more details regarding specific locations related to the party specified in the NAD- segment, e.g. internal site/building number.

segmentGroup.documentation: Segment Group 3: A segment group giving references and where necessary, date information only relevant to the specified party.

segment.name: Reference
segment.documentation: RFF, A segment identifying the reference by its number and where appropriate a line number within a document.

segment.name: Date/time/period
segment.documentation: DTM, A segment specifying the date and/or time of the reference. The specified date should be in 'yymmdd' format unless all parties agree that there is a functional requirement for an alternative format.

segmentGroup.documentation: Segment Group 4: A group of segments giving contact details of the specific person or department within the party identified in the NAD segment.

segment.name: Contact information
segment.documentation: CTA, A segment to identify a person or department, and their function, to whom communications should be directed.

segment.name: Communication contact
segment.documentation: COM, A segment to identify a communication type and number for the contact specified in the CTA segment.

segmentGroup.documentation: Segment Group 5: -SG20-SG30 A group of segments providing the relevant quality data for the specified product.

segment.name: Line item
segment.documentation: LIN, A segment identifying the line item by its number and additionally, identifying the product involved by a product identification number. Other product identification numbers are specified in the following PIA segment, e.g. Customer part number, etc.

segment.name: Additional product id
segment.documentation: PIA, A segment providing additional product identification to that specified in the LIN segment, e.g. Buyer part number.

segment.name: Item description
segment.documentation: IMD, A segment for describing the product involved. This segment should be used for products that cannot be identified by a product code or article number.

segment.name: Measurements
segment.documentation: MEA, A segment to allow physical measurements and dimensions to be stated, where this is required for identification of the product.

segment.name: Physical sample description
segment.documentation: PSD, A segment to define the physical sample parameters, associated with a test, resulting in discrete measurements. If used in this position, the values apply to all following values of product properties.

segment.name: Sampling parameters for summary statiC 1 DTM Date/time/period
segment.documentation: SPS, A segment to define the sampling parameters associated with summary statistics reported. If used in this position, the values apply to all following values of product properties.

segment.name: Quantity
segment.documentation: DTM, A segment specifying date/time/period details to the line item only. Any specified date should be in 'yymmdd' format unless all parties agree that there is a functional requirement for an alternative format.

segment.name: Free text
segment.documentation: QTY, A segment to enable quantity information to be specified.

segmentGroup.documentation: FTX, A segment with free text in coded or clear form, to give further clarification, when required, for the line item. In computer to computer exchanges such text will normally require the receiver to handle this segment manually.

segment.documentation: Segment Group 10: A group of segments to provide details of the test methods, employed including any circumstances, test devices, references and dates.

segmentGroup.documentation: DTM, A segment specifying the date, and when relevant, the time of an activity identified by the date/time qualifier, e.g. test date/time.

segment.name: Characteristic/class id
segment.documentation: Segment Group 12: A group of segments to be used to define a class of properties, the individual properties within that class and the related data (e.g. discrete values, statistical information, test methods). When this segment group is used, the data is directly related to the product specified.

segment.name: Physical sample description
segment.documentation:
CCI, To specify the general class and/or the individual properties on which the Quality Data is being reported. Note: within the CCI-segment Property Class Identification (7769) or Measurement Dimension, coded (6313) or Characteristic identification (7751) must be present.
If Property Class identification (7769) AND measurement Dimension, coded (6313) are present, then Characteristic identification (7751) is not allowed.
If only Property Class identification is used within the CCI-segment, then the individual properties must be specified within the related STA/MEA-segments.
The data element Characteristic Text (7750) should only be used to enhance the meaning of the code value (e.g. if no specific code available and code value ZZ (mutually defined) is used then Description can be used to further describe the Product Characteristics.
NB: The Class identification element in this segment is only used to specify the product characteristic class, e.g. Chemistry or Physical Dimensions.
